HEADWORD: Masterfully
<hw>Mas"ter*ful*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a masterful manner;
imperiously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A lawless and rebellious man who held lands <qex>masterfully</qex>
and in high contempt of the royal authority.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

